==English==

===Etymology===
[[Retronym]] for '''watch''', coined after the invention of the digital watch to refer specifically to the type of watch existing before then.

===Alternative forms===
*'''analogue watch''' (''UK'')
*'''analog watch''' (''US'')

===Noun===
'''[[analogue]] [[watch]]''' (''plural:'' '''analogue watches''')

# A watch that displays time by means of a dial and hands, in [[contradistinction]] to a [[digital watch]].